WEBVTT

1
00:00:06.000 --> 00:00:12.074
Watch Online Movies and Series for FREE
www.osdb.link/lm

2
00:00:41.389 --> 00:00:45.553
Letters From IWO Jima

3
00:00:55.670 --> 00:00:59.333
IWO JIMA

4
3
00:02:10.478 --> 00:02:13.970
How did those soldiers ever manage
to dig out these tunnels?

5
00:02:14.849 --> 00:02:16.248
Let's get a rotation in here.

6
00:02:16.418 --> 00:02:18.318
Hey. I found something!

7
00:02:30.398 --> 00:02:33.162
IWO JIMA

8
7
00:02:33.335 --> 00:02:34.427
Hanako...

9
00:02:35.403 --> 00:02:37.337
We soldiers dig.

10
00:02:37.839 --> 00:02:40.501
We dig all day.

11
00:02:42.510 --> 00:02:44.569
This is the hole that we will fight...

12
00:02:45.380 --> 00:02:47.109
and die in.

13
00:02:49.451 --> 00:02:50.918
Hanako...

14
00:02:51.453 --> 00:02:54.718
am I digging my own grave?

15
00:03:28.538 --> 00:03:32.065
Today. I head for the post
where my men await.

16
00:03:32.976 --> 00:03:37.174
I am determined to serve
and give my life for my country.

17
00:03:38.315 --> 00:03:40.840
I believe I have organized
everything at home...

18
00:03:41.017 --> 00:03:45.647
but I am sorry I wasn't able to attend
to the kitchen floor before I left.

19
00:03:46.323 --> 00:03:48.086
I had all the intention...

20
00:03:48.258 --> 00:03:50.590
but had to leave
without having the time...

21
00:03:51.027 --> 00:03:53.086
and I am still worried about it.

22
00:03:53.363 --> 00:03:56.491
So make sure to have
Taro take care of it promptly.

23
00:04:02.572 --> 00:04:06.531
Damn this island!
The Americans can have it.

24
00:04:09.012 --> 00:04:10.343
Nothing grows here.

25
00:04:11.281 --> 00:04:16.344
It smells. It's hot. There are too many
damn bugs. and there's no water.

26
00:04:18.622 --> 00:04:22.422
This island is part
of Japan's sacred homeland.

27
00:04:22.726 --> 00:04:24.785
There's nothing sacred about this island.

28
00:04:28.365 --> 00:04:29.525
Saigo.

29
00:04:29.933 --> 00:04:33.767
We should just give the island
to the Americans...

30
00:04:34.037 --> 00:04:35.470
and then we can go home.

31
00:04:39.042 --> 00:04:40.134
Saigo!

32
00:04:41.978 --> 00:04:43.309
What did you say. soldier?

33
00:04:44.981 --> 00:04:48.439
I said if we beat the Americans.
then we can go home.

34
00:04:49.619 --> 00:04:51.746
You there. is that what he said?

35
00:04:53.223 --> 00:04:55.487
Yes. sir.

36
00:06:18.341 --> 00:06:19.399
I'm Kuribayashi.

37
00:06:19.643 --> 00:06:22.305
Welcome. General.
I am Admiral ohsugi.

38
00:06:22.679 --> 00:06:25.011
How long have you been
waiting here for me?

39
00:06:26.149 --> 00:06:27.514
Three hours. sir.

40
00:06:27.684 --> 00:06:29.015
Sorry to hear that.

41
00:06:29.219 --> 00:06:33.747
They wouldn't allow me to wire my arrival
after what happened to Admiral Yamamoto.

42
00:06:34.024 --> 00:06:35.150
I understand. sir.

43
00:06:35.392 --> 00:06:37.257
This is my aide. Lieutenant Fujita.

44
00:06:37.894 --> 00:06:40.385
What's the matter. Admiral?
You don't look very well.

45
00:06:40.597 --> 00:06:43.930
It's nothing. sir. The water
doesn't agree with me here.

46
00:06:44.100 --> 00:06:45.590
Sorry to hear that.

47
00:06:46.269 --> 00:06:47.759
This way to your quarters.

48
00:06:48.071 --> 00:06:50.665
Admiral. I want to make a round
of the island first.

49
00:06:50.874 --> 00:06:52.899
Shall I fetch a vehicle?

50
00:06:53.076 --> 00:06:55.044
No. let's walk.

51
00:06:56.046 --> 00:06:57.673
Walking is good for the health.

52
00:06:57.847 --> 00:07:00.008
It might be just what you need. ohsugi.

53
00:07:15.932 --> 00:07:17.695
So that's Suribachi.

54
00:07:26.743 --> 00:07:27.801
You unpatriotic...

55
00:07:28.545 --> 00:07:29.876
no-good peasants!

56
00:07:30.313 --> 00:07:31.575
Hey. stop it!

57
00:07:35.318 --> 00:07:36.410
Stand up!

58
00:07:37.420 --> 00:07:38.785
What are you doing?

59
00:07:41.491 --> 00:07:42.822
These soldiers...

60
00:07:45.695 --> 00:07:47.686
were conspiring
with unpatriotic words. sir.

61
00:07:48.732 --> 00:07:49.858
I see.

62
00:07:50.100 --> 00:07:52.728
And. captain. do you have
such an excess of soldiers...

63
00:07:52.902 --> 00:07:55.530
that you could put two
of them out of commission?

64
00:07:56.439 --> 00:07:57.633
No. sir.

65
00:07:58.575 --> 00:08:00.202
Then stop beating them.

66
00:08:00.577 --> 00:08:02.875
Deny their lunch rations instead.

67
00:08:03.413 --> 00:08:07.110
A good captain uses his brain.
not just his whip.

68
00:08:12.088 --> 00:08:13.817
What is all this?

69
00:08:14.457 --> 00:08:15.651
All this?

70
00:08:15.959 --> 00:08:17.256
Trenches. sir.

71
00:08:17.961 --> 00:08:19.724
Why are the men digging trenches here?

72
00:08:20.263 --> 00:08:23.096
This is where the Americans
are expected to land.

73
00:08:24.934 --> 00:08:26.663
Have them stop immediately.

74
00:08:27.470 --> 00:08:28.903
But. General...

75
00:08:29.506 --> 00:08:30.734
And. captain...

76
00:08:31.574 --> 00:08:33.565
make sure these men get proper breaks.

77
00:08:33.910 --> 00:08:36.344
They look like they're from Mars.

78
00:08:49.092 --> 00:08:50.320
Stop digging!

79
00:09:07.811 --> 00:09:09.142
Just as well.

80
00:09:10.346 --> 00:09:13.179
My stomach has been
bothering me anyway.

81
00:09:14.384 --> 00:09:16.614
A toast to General Kuribayashi...

82
00:09:18.321 --> 00:09:19.982
a fine commander.

83
00:09:23.993 --> 00:09:25.654
Better than sake!

84
00:09:26.496 --> 00:09:28.225
I heard he lived in America.

85
00:09:29.466 --> 00:09:31.900
Maybe that's why he
doesn't want us digging trenches.

86
00:09:32.068 --> 00:09:33.797
Maybe he likes Americans.

87
00:09:34.037 --> 00:09:37.632
No. stupid.
He studied the Americans.

88
00:09:39.642 --> 00:09:42.509
So now he knows how to beat them.

89
00:09:44.214 --> 00:09:46.011
I heard from someone in the 204th...

90
00:09:46.750 --> 00:09:51.312
that another general was
supposed to command the island...

91
00:09:52.021 --> 00:09:55.149
but he didn't want the job.

92
00:09:56.593 --> 00:10:00.654
So Premier Tojo gave it
to Kuribayashi instead.

93
00:10:02.031 --> 00:10:05.933
Nozaki. you hear a lot of things...

94
00:10:07.370 --> 00:10:09.531
but your ears are full of wax!

95
00:10:11.207 --> 00:10:15.234
Anyway. you can't trust anyone
from the 204th.

96
00:10:15.411 --> 00:10:17.276
They're part of the Navy.

97
00:10:17.614 --> 00:10:20.606
I think this Kuribayashi
must be a superb general.

98
00:10:21.184 --> 00:10:22.378
Look...

99
00:10:23.119 --> 00:10:28.421
we're not digging those damn trenches
in the sand anymore. are we?

100
00:10:44.941 --> 00:10:47.933
This heat is more than I had anticipated.

101
00:10:52.715 --> 00:10:57.743
This island is bigger than I thought.
I'm exhausted.

102
00:11:05.395 --> 00:11:06.555
Ito. reporting for duty.

103
00:11:06.729 --> 00:11:08.754
Thank you for coming right away.

104
00:11:09.999 --> 00:11:12.627
How much air force
do we have available?

105
00:11:12.802 --> 00:11:15.430
41 Zekes and 13 bombers. sir.

106
00:11:15.605 --> 00:11:16.594
Is that all?

107
00:11:16.773 --> 00:11:20.834
In order to support Saipan.
we lost 66 planes a few days ago.

108
00:11:22.145 --> 00:11:26.479
We will have to rely on support
from the combined Fleet then.

109
00:11:28.852 --> 00:11:30.444
Is this the current defense plan?

110
00:11:36.159 --> 00:11:39.094
And what about the Army troops?
Where will they be stationed?

111
00:11:41.931 --> 00:11:43.796
I don't know exactly.

112
00:11:43.967 --> 00:11:46.834
They are under independent
command of colonel Adachi.

113
00:11:47.003 --> 00:11:49.369
You have not coordinated
your plans with the Army?

114
00:11:49.539 --> 00:11:52.303
According to Navy rules.
until the enemy lands...

115
00:11:52.475 --> 00:11:55.376
This is a real war!
You are aware of that. aren't you?

116
00:12:01.517 --> 00:12:02.677
This will not work.

117
00:12:02.852 --> 00:12:05.320
You are concentrating all
your efforts on the beaches.

118
00:12:05.722 --> 00:12:08.919
- Move the artillery to higher ground.
- But. sir. we just had them...

119
00:12:09.092 --> 00:12:10.684
moved down to the beaches.

120
00:12:10.860 --> 00:12:12.327
Well. move them back.

121
00:12:14.697 --> 00:12:17.291
Coordinate with the Army
and have them start immediately.

122
00:12:17.467 --> 00:12:20.527
Fortifications at Suribachi are the priority.

123
00:12:21.004 --> 00:12:22.301
I'm going to walk some more.

124
00:12:22.505 --> 00:12:25.372
- It's pitch black out there. sir.
- I know.

125
00:12:36.386 --> 00:12:37.876
This one is trouble.

126
00:12:39.856 --> 00:12:43.189
Army commanders usually are. sir.

127
00:13:25.902 --> 00:13:27.267
Another letter?

128
00:13:27.470 --> 00:13:30.564
You know that the mail only goes out
when there's a boat available?

129
00:13:31.040 --> 00:13:32.439
I have a lot of family.

130
00:13:32.976 --> 00:13:35.774
Then how come all your letters
are addressed to your wife?

131
00:13:37.380 --> 00:13:38.540
Nosey!

132
00:13:38.748 --> 00:13:40.375
Here. let me do you a favor.

133
00:13:40.917 --> 00:13:44.080
Otherwise. your letters
will never make it through.

134
00:13:45.254 --> 00:13:46.949
Hey. what are you doing?

135
00:13:47.390 --> 00:13:50.826
I used to work at the censorship office
in Tokyo before I was transferred.

136
00:13:51.794 --> 00:13:53.591
You mean demoted.

137
00:13:54.564 --> 00:13:58.091
"To Hanako: We soldiers dig.
We dig all day."

138
00:13:58.301 --> 00:14:00.963
No. no. no. This will never pass.

139
00:14:02.972 --> 00:14:04.564
Give me that back!

140
00:14:13.349 --> 00:14:17.752
There. You'll thank me
for this later. Saigo.

141
00:14:21.591 --> 00:14:22.751
Next!

142
00:14:29.265 --> 00:14:30.493
Good!

143
00:14:57.060 --> 00:14:58.652
Are you blind?

144
00:15:00.196 --> 00:15:01.993
Can't you see the target?

145
00:15:03.332 --> 00:15:06.665
Even my six-year-old could
shoot better than you do.

146
00:15:07.904 --> 00:15:09.030
Do it again!

147
00:15:15.078 --> 00:15:18.570
You're an embarrassment!
You call yourself an lmperial soldier?

148
00:15:20.516 --> 00:15:24.077
Tonight you will clean the boots
of your entire troop.

149
00:15:24.253 --> 00:15:25.345
Go to the rear!

150
00:15:27.857 --> 00:15:31.486
They should learn to clean their guns
properly. rather than their boots.

151
00:16:07.063 --> 00:16:08.894
What are those tanks doing here?

152
00:16:09.232 --> 00:16:13.225
Those are out of commission. sir.
They are waiting for parts.

153
00:16:13.436 --> 00:16:16.064
- For how long?
- About a month. sir.

154
00:16:35.925 --> 00:16:39.292
Taro. America is filled with cars.

155
00:16:40.429 --> 00:16:44.593
I have to be very careful
when I cross the street...

156
00:16:45.434 --> 00:16:47.994
there are so many cars everywhere.

157
00:16:49.071 --> 00:16:53.064
Taro. are you behaving yourself
and listening to your mother?

158
00:16:53.809 --> 00:16:55.436
I miss you.

159
00:17:05.488 --> 00:17:08.753
These civilians need to be
evacuated as soon as possible.

160
00:17:09.959 --> 00:17:11.688
Yes. sir.

161
00:18:13.022 --> 00:18:14.046
Hanako...

162
00:18:14.991 --> 00:18:16.891
we have a celebrity here.

163
00:18:17.493 --> 00:18:20.826
Baron Nishi. the Olympic gold medalist
in horse jumping.

164
00:18:22.231 --> 00:18:25.029
He will lead the 26th tank regiment...

165
00:18:25.701 --> 00:18:28.568
and has just arrived from Tokyo.

166
00:18:43.552 --> 00:18:47.716
Nishi is very handsome. and there are
rumors of his womanizing skills.

167
00:18:48.958 --> 00:18:53.224
But there are no women
left on the island to woo.

168
00:19:19.588 --> 00:19:22.614
Lieutenant colonel Nishi!
You brought your horse.

169
00:19:23.225 --> 00:19:24.385
From chichi Jima.

170
00:19:30.466 --> 00:19:32.559
I used to be a cavalryman myself.
you know.

171
00:19:32.735 --> 00:19:34.794
Of course. I know.

172
00:19:35.071 --> 00:19:38.472
I've been looking forward
to serving under you.

173
00:19:39.075 --> 00:19:41.566
One who understands horses
the way I do.

174
00:19:41.744 --> 00:19:45.908
When we used to ride horses
through the battlefield...

175
00:19:46.082 --> 00:19:47.947
those were the good old days...

176
00:19:49.352 --> 00:19:51.411
not like these mechanized contraptions.

177
00:19:52.755 --> 00:19:54.950
I could send for another horse...

178
00:19:55.825 --> 00:19:57.315
and we could ride together.

179
00:19:57.493 --> 00:19:59.154
I'm afraid my riding days are over.

180
00:20:00.763 --> 00:20:05.530
But tell me about this famous horse
of yours that you won the olympics with.

181
00:20:06.435 --> 00:20:07.766
My stallion. Uranus.

182
00:20:19.148 --> 00:20:22.276
Oh. yes. this horse has a fine back.

183
00:20:25.855 --> 00:20:27.823
I bought him in Italy.

184
00:20:28.657 --> 00:20:30.648
They were happy to get rid of him.

185
00:20:30.826 --> 00:20:33.556
He was such a wild horse.

186
00:20:34.563 --> 00:20:38.863
No one could tame the beast.
but I told them...

187
00:20:39.034 --> 00:20:40.968
such a headstrong horse...

188
00:20:41.370 --> 00:20:44.737
is a perfect match for me.

189
00:20:49.145 --> 00:20:51.807
Come dine with me tonight.
I feel like having a drink.

190
00:20:52.715 --> 00:20:54.205
I think that can be arranged.

191
00:21:03.926 --> 00:21:06.360
How did you manage to get
the Johnnie walker?

192
00:21:07.029 --> 00:21:08.758
I drank some already.

193
00:21:15.104 --> 00:21:17.902
I'm sorry. This is all we have.

194
00:21:18.073 --> 00:21:20.200
That's fine. as long as we have this.

195
00:21:24.513 --> 00:21:26.344
What is this empty plate?

196
00:21:27.516 --> 00:21:32.010
I have told our cook that all officers will
have the same rations and food as our men.

197
00:21:32.188 --> 00:21:35.248
I'm sorry. but serving three dishes
is regulation.

198
00:21:36.292 --> 00:21:40.023
Oh. but of course we have the right to be
served more than three dishes per meal.

199
00:21:40.196 --> 00:21:41.424
You're absolutely right.

200
00:21:52.575 --> 00:21:54.406
When you think about it...

201
00:21:54.777 --> 00:21:59.077
it is regrettable that most of the
combined Fleet was destroyed.

202
00:22:00.649 --> 00:22:02.412
We still have some battleships left...

203
00:22:02.585 --> 00:22:07.579
but we have very little striking power
from the air or sea.

204
00:22:08.724 --> 00:22:10.214
Nishi. what do you mean?

205
00:22:13.562 --> 00:22:18.158
So you have not heard about
the Mariana battle?

206
00:22:19.268 --> 00:22:24.262
Admiral ozawa's carrier and boat planes
were destroyed.

207
00:22:26.842 --> 00:22:28.241
The lmperial headquarters...

208
00:22:28.911 --> 00:22:31.778
is deceiving not just the people.
but us as well.

209
00:22:32.181 --> 00:22:34.945
If you want my honest opinion. General...

210
00:22:36.652 --> 00:22:38.586
the best thing to do...

211
00:22:39.421 --> 00:22:43.949
would be to sink the island
to the bottom of the sea.

212
00:22:46.428 --> 00:22:48.293
And yet. you still came?

213
00:22:51.467 --> 00:22:52.525
Well...

214
00:22:52.968 --> 00:22:57.962
I figured your men were going to need
all the tanks that I could bring.

215
00:23:46.922 --> 00:23:48.389
This must be it.

216
00:23:48.791 --> 00:23:50.759
Yes. the enemy must land here.

217
00:23:56.231 --> 00:23:57.289
Run!

218
00:23:58.367 --> 00:23:59.959
Like you were one of the Americans!

219
00:24:00.202 --> 00:24:02.102
Go on! Which direction would you take?

220
00:24:31.000 --> 00:24:32.228
Hey...

221
00:24:33.335 --> 00:24:35.428
I think your general has gone mad.

222
00:24:39.408 --> 00:24:41.137
Look at the gun he has.

223
00:24:45.748 --> 00:24:48.740
He probably took it
from a dead American.

224
00:24:49.852 --> 00:24:51.285
Maybe.

225
00:24:59.361 --> 00:25:00.692
Break time is over.

226
00:25:01.430 --> 00:25:02.658
Back to work!

227
00:25:07.336 --> 00:25:09.031
Are you all right. Kashiwara?

228
00:25:09.638 --> 00:25:11.265
You look pale.

229
00:25:13.042 --> 00:25:15.135
I'm fine. It's just the damn water.

230
00:25:15.844 --> 00:25:19.644
But... l... really... need to go.

231
00:25:39.068 --> 00:25:41.298
There will be a major change
in our strategy.

232
00:25:41.970 --> 00:25:46.703
We will dig caves in the Motoyama.
Higashiyama. and Suribachi-yama areas.

233
00:25:47.242 --> 00:25:51.645
We will build these underground
fortifications. and fight to the end.

234
00:25:51.947 --> 00:25:55.144
- What about the beach defenses. sir?
- Not needed.

235
00:25:56.585 --> 00:26:00.316
But. sir. the beach trenches
are our first line of defense.

236
00:26:00.489 --> 00:26:03.856
Without the beach trenches.
how do you expect us to win?

237
00:26:04.026 --> 00:26:09.020
Hayashi. do you know how many cars
America produces in a year?

238
00:26:09.198 --> 00:26:10.358
Five million.

239
00:26:10.833 --> 00:26:13.893
The Americans' technological advancements
cannot be underestimated.

240
00:26:14.069 --> 00:26:16.867
They will cross the beaches eventually.

241
00:26:18.440 --> 00:26:20.965
If we waste our soldiers there.
there is no hope for victory.

242
00:26:21.143 --> 00:26:22.906
It is inevitable that men will die...

243
00:26:23.512 --> 00:26:26.743
but I never heard of an island operation
without beach fortifications.

244
00:26:26.915 --> 00:26:30.544
General. it will be a futile waste of time
to start digging tunnels now.

245
00:26:30.719 --> 00:26:32.346
We should force the enemy
near the island...

246
00:26:32.521 --> 00:26:34.682
and launch a pincer drive
from the sea and air.

247
00:26:34.857 --> 00:26:37.223
I agree. That makes the most sense.

248
00:26:37.426 --> 00:26:38.518
Ohsugi...

249
00:26:39.561 --> 00:26:41.256
doesn't the Navy know?

250
00:26:45.300 --> 00:26:48.792
The combined Fleet has been completely
destroyed off the Marianas.

251
00:26:49.037 --> 00:26:51.096
The island is now isolated.

252
00:26:56.678 --> 00:27:00.375
What's more. I received a new order from
the lmperial headquarters this morning.

253
00:27:00.749 --> 00:27:04.947
The remaining fighter planes are to be
sent back to Tokyo to defend the mainland.

254
00:27:05.120 --> 00:27:08.146
Outrageous! How are we to fight?

255
00:27:11.927 --> 00:27:15.829
We do not have time for discussion.
We should head back.

256
00:27:48.831 --> 00:27:49.991
Dear Mother...

257
00:27:51.633 --> 00:27:54.864
I have been commissioned
to a new troop today.

258
00:27:56.638 --> 00:28:00.130
I cannot talk about this transfer now.

259
00:28:01.643 --> 00:28:03.440
Take good care of yourself.

260
00:28:17.626 --> 00:28:18.957
Look at this picture.

261
00:28:22.197 --> 00:28:23.892
That's some fancy castle.

262
00:28:25.200 --> 00:28:27.862
You know who this castle was built for?

263
00:28:28.704 --> 00:28:30.501
Someone who was already dead.

264
00:28:32.541 --> 00:28:35.066
They must have had
a lot of money back then...

265
00:28:35.611 --> 00:28:37.704
to build a castle like that
for a dead person.

266
00:28:39.348 --> 00:28:41.543
Why are you reading that book anyway?

267
00:28:42.150 --> 00:28:44.846
We're never going to war over there.

268
00:28:46.054 --> 00:28:49.114
We'll be lucky if we even get
a hole in the ground when we're dead.

269
00:28:49.858 --> 00:28:51.849
Don't talk about that. It's bad luck.

270
00:28:57.532 --> 00:28:59.329
Is this the 312th?

271
00:28:59.668 --> 00:29:01.067
That's right.

272
00:29:01.937 --> 00:29:04.531
I'm Nozaki. This is Saigo.

273
00:29:07.175 --> 00:29:09.871
Shimizu. you can put your bedroll there.

274
00:29:14.349 --> 00:29:16.214
There's an empty space in the back.

275
00:29:17.853 --> 00:29:19.081
Don't mind him.

276
00:29:20.355 --> 00:29:23.791
His friend Kashiwara just died.

277
00:29:24.693 --> 00:29:26.456
That used to be his spot.

278
00:29:34.136 --> 00:29:36.070
But we are all going to die.

279
00:29:36.872 --> 00:29:38.863
That's the plan. isn't it?

280
00:29:41.109 --> 00:29:43.100
For our country. it is an honor.

281
00:29:45.414 --> 00:29:47.712
Kashiwara died of honorable dysentery.

282
00:29:49.151 --> 00:29:51.813
Shimizu. where are you from?

283
00:29:54.156 --> 00:29:55.418
Kanagawa-ken.

284
00:29:57.125 --> 00:29:59.150
Ozawa is from there. aren't you?

285
00:30:00.228 --> 00:30:01.559
That's right.

286
00:30:05.500 --> 00:30:07.127
Where were you trained?

287
00:30:07.903 --> 00:30:10.838
Maybe we were at the same school?

288
00:30:11.907 --> 00:30:12.965
No.

289
00:30:13.675 --> 00:30:15.836
I trained in Tokyo.

290
00:30:16.278 --> 00:30:18.610
I trained in Tokyo. too. Where?

291
00:30:26.021 --> 00:30:28.182
The Koho Kimmu Yoin Yoseijo.

292
00:30:39.968 --> 00:30:41.265
Hey...

293
00:30:42.738 --> 00:30:45.002
why do you think they put
a Kempeitai in our unit?

294
00:30:45.173 --> 00:30:46.538
I don't know.

295
00:30:50.879 --> 00:30:54.042
He's not wearing the white armband.
He's not Kempeitai.

296
00:30:55.851 --> 00:30:58.012
He went to the Kempeitai
military academy.

297
00:30:59.121 --> 00:31:01.055
Maybe he was kicked out.

298
00:31:04.793 --> 00:31:06.954
He acts like a Kempeitai.

299
00:31:11.533 --> 00:31:14.001
Look at his holster.
That's not standard issue.

300
00:31:16.171 --> 00:31:19.504
He's been put here to spy on us.

301
00:31:21.243 --> 00:31:23.734
Why would he spy on us?

302
00:31:25.580 --> 00:31:29.209
Maybe it's those letters
you've been writing.

303
00:31:31.553 --> 00:31:33.145
You should be careful.

304
00:31:59.781 --> 00:32:01.874
Weed soup again?

305
00:32:03.952 --> 00:32:07.444
Kuribayashi is conserving
our food supplies for the battle.

306
00:32:08.356 --> 00:32:12.087
We'll be dead
before the Americans even get here.

307
00:32:13.929 --> 00:32:17.057
And you would think that with all my
war effort contributions...

308
00:32:17.299 --> 00:32:20.894
we should be eating kasutera cakes
or sandwiches.

309
00:32:22.304 --> 00:32:23.464
What?

310
00:32:24.239 --> 00:32:29.472
I ran a bakery in ohmiya with my wife.

311
00:32:29.911 --> 00:32:31.742
Back when we could still get sugar...

312
00:32:33.215 --> 00:32:37.811
we sold ampan and kasutera cakes.

313
00:32:45.727 --> 00:32:49.629
However. his Kempeitai brethren...

314
00:32:50.665 --> 00:32:53.065
used to come and take
whatever they wanted.

315
00:32:56.438 --> 00:32:58.133
For the war...

316
00:32:59.975 --> 00:33:01.772
For the country...

317
00:33:04.246 --> 00:33:05.804
why bread?

318
00:33:08.984 --> 00:33:14.286
We ran into those types
at our clothing store as well.

319
00:33:16.625 --> 00:33:18.923
When we started making sandwiches...

320
00:33:20.428 --> 00:33:22.623
they took those. too.

321
00:33:24.699 --> 00:33:28.294
And when we ran out of meat
and just had bread. they still came.

322
00:33:33.475 --> 00:33:37.809
Eventually. they took all of our
baking equipment for the metal...

323
00:33:40.482 --> 00:33:43.610
and we were out of business.

324
00:33:47.522 --> 00:33:49.319
I should have been a fisherman.

325
00:33:52.694 --> 00:33:54.889
It must have been hard on your wife...

326
00:33:57.799 --> 00:34:00.324
without the shop
and without her husband.

327
00:34:34.035 --> 00:34:37.994
Tell them to go away.
We have nothing to sell.

328
00:34:44.045 --> 00:34:47.776
Congratulations! Your husband
is going to war.

329
00:35:02.530 --> 00:35:04.293
Thank you very much.

330
00:35:04.966 --> 00:35:08.800
I'm happy to serve the country.

331
00:35:12.907 --> 00:35:16.399
Prayers for your eternal success at arms.

332
00:35:16.978 --> 00:35:21.438
I beg of you! We have only each other.

333
00:35:25.153 --> 00:35:27.644
This is not the time.

334
00:35:29.724 --> 00:35:34.388
We have all sent our husbands
and sons to war.

335
00:35:35.230 --> 00:35:39.428
We all have to do our part.

336
00:35:43.271 --> 00:35:46.069
At least you'll have a little one
to carry on your name.

337
00:35:59.387 --> 00:36:01.912
I can't eat with you like that.

338
00:36:04.926 --> 00:36:09.226
What am I going to do after you die?

339
00:36:15.603 --> 00:36:17.833
I'm not in the coffin yet.

340
00:36:20.642 --> 00:36:24.408
The men never come home.
not even a soul.

341
00:36:27.182 --> 00:36:29.082
They'll never let you come home.

342
00:36:31.119 --> 00:36:32.518
Don't worry.

343
00:36:35.023 --> 00:36:36.650
And now. with the baby.

344
00:37:00.348 --> 00:37:01.645
Can you hear me?

345
00:37:03.385 --> 00:37:04.682
It's Dad.

346
00:37:07.655 --> 00:37:08.713
Listen.

347
00:37:11.693 --> 00:37:15.390
Don't tell anyone
what I'm telling you now.

348
00:37:17.699 --> 00:37:18.859
It's a secret.

349
00:37:34.082 --> 00:37:35.310
Your dad...

350
00:37:39.154 --> 00:37:41.179
is going to come home for you.

351
00:38:37.445 --> 00:38:38.639
Hurry up!

352
00:38:42.083 --> 00:38:43.607
The enemy approaches!

353
00:38:54.329 --> 00:38:55.728
This is ridiculous!

354
00:38:56.297 --> 00:38:58.595
Why waste time digging these tunnels?

355
00:38:59.267 --> 00:39:01.326
They are all going to die anyway.

356
00:39:01.936 --> 00:39:05.497
At least he conceded
to the pillboxes on the beach.

357
00:39:18.453 --> 00:39:20.148
You wanted to see me. sir?

358
00:39:21.322 --> 00:39:22.846
Care for a drink?

359
00:39:28.329 --> 00:39:30.627
You have been looking
quite pale these days.

360
00:39:34.135 --> 00:39:37.969
It's the water. It has
never agreed with me.

361
00:39:38.373 --> 00:39:39.601
That's not good.

362
00:39:41.142 --> 00:39:44.168
Why don't you go back
to the mainland to recoup?

363
00:39:45.780 --> 00:39:49.944
I have commissioned Admiral Ichimaru
to take your place.

364
00:39:51.653 --> 00:39:53.951
We are wasting time
digging these tunnels.

365
00:39:54.656 --> 00:39:58.786
General. the island won't last
five days without fleet support.

366
00:40:00.361 --> 00:40:02.727
We should fight to the death.

367
00:40:04.165 --> 00:40:08.499
The tunnel-digging may be futile.

368
00:40:09.304 --> 00:40:13.206
Maybe the stand on IWO will be futile.

369
00:40:13.675 --> 00:40:15.870
Maybe the whole war is futile.

370
00:40:16.044 --> 00:40:17.705
But will you give up then?

371
00:40:18.046 --> 00:40:20.173
We will defend this island
until we are dead!

372
00:40:20.348 --> 00:40:22.578
Until the very last soldier is dead!

373
00:40:23.418 --> 00:40:27.752
If our children can live safely
for one more day...

374
00:40:28.022 --> 00:40:31.150
it would be worth the one more day
that we defend this island!

375
00:40:32.060 --> 00:40:33.254
Ohsugi...

376
00:40:33.861 --> 00:40:37.854
if you have an ounce
of pride left as an officer...

377
00:40:38.733 --> 00:40:40.064
I beg of you...

378
00:40:40.702 --> 00:40:43.830
go back to headquarters
and ask them to send support.

379
00:41:08.563 --> 00:41:12.260
So the rumor is true?
I couldn't believe it.

380
00:41:13.701 --> 00:41:17.535
I'm grateful to be leaving this island.

381
00:41:19.273 --> 00:41:21.264
We may have had our differences...

382
00:41:22.443 --> 00:41:25.310
but I'm truly sorry to see you go.

383
00:41:26.814 --> 00:41:29.977
General Hayashi. it is up to you now.

384
00:41:31.586 --> 00:41:36.455
Kuribayashi belongs behind a desk.
not commanding war.

385
00:41:37.225 --> 00:41:38.590
I understand.

386
00:41:38.926 --> 00:41:42.453
There are many of us
who agree with you. sir.

387
00:41:57.578 --> 00:41:58.567
Listen.

388
00:41:59.080 --> 00:42:02.777
The Americans are likely to land here.

389
00:42:04.285 --> 00:42:06.685
Crossfire positions will be here...

390
00:42:07.855 --> 00:42:08.844
here...

391
00:42:09.991 --> 00:42:11.151
and here.

392
00:42:12.593 --> 00:42:13.855
The fact is...

393
00:42:14.028 --> 00:42:20.331
we are completely
outnumbered in every sector.

394
00:42:22.136 --> 00:42:24.127
But we have a great advantage.

395
00:42:25.139 --> 00:42:27.699
Can anyone tell me what that is?

396
00:42:33.314 --> 00:42:36.306
The Americans are weak-willed
and inferior to Japanese soldiers.

397
00:42:36.484 --> 00:42:37.951
Very good. Shimizu.

398
00:42:38.853 --> 00:42:40.343
Why is that?

399
00:42:40.655 --> 00:42:42.213
They are not as disciplined...

400
00:42:42.390 --> 00:42:45.120
and they let their emotions
interfere with their duty.

401
00:42:45.293 --> 00:42:46.555
That is correct.

402
00:42:50.231 --> 00:42:53.223
Here is the uniform
of an American medic.

403
00:42:54.702 --> 00:42:55.964
He should be your target.

404
00:42:56.804 --> 00:43:00.865
For Americans will risk the lives
of many soldiers to save this one.

405
00:43:01.809 --> 00:43:02.867
Understood?

406
00:43:14.422 --> 00:43:17.357
General. may I speak with you?

407
00:43:19.761 --> 00:43:22.195
Please keep an eye on
Major General Hayashi.

408
00:43:24.432 --> 00:43:26.662
Thank you for your concern. Nishi...

409
00:43:27.001 --> 00:43:30.027
but we don't have any time to waste.

410
00:43:30.371 --> 00:43:33.602
We must think about what
we can do at this moment.

411
00:43:36.911 --> 00:43:38.378
Admiral Ichimaru.

412
00:43:41.549 --> 00:43:43.414
Reporting for duty. sir.

413
00:43:44.418 --> 00:43:46.045
Excuse me.

414
00:43:46.454 --> 00:43:49.048
Thank you for coming
on such short notice.

415
00:45:47.508 --> 00:45:48.668
Jupiter!

416
00:45:51.512 --> 00:45:52.809
Jupiter.

417
00:46:44.065 --> 00:46:45.259
Yamazaki...

418
00:46:46.300 --> 00:46:49.428
what are you doing just
sitting there? Help us...

419
00:47:29.410 --> 00:47:32.243
I think he's writing about us in his reports.

420
00:47:33.447 --> 00:47:35.108
He's just writing a letter.

421
00:47:35.616 --> 00:47:38.483
It's been two months. Nozaki.

422
00:47:39.954 --> 00:47:41.751
He would have reported us by now.

423
00:47:41.922 --> 00:47:43.651
How can you be sure?

424
00:47:51.665 --> 00:47:54.463
Will they ever stop?

425
00:47:54.935 --> 00:47:57.961
Day and night. day and night...

426
00:48:00.341 --> 00:48:02.309
It's driving me crazy!

427
00:48:03.144 --> 00:48:07.513
If the damn Americans
are going to invade...

428
00:48:09.383 --> 00:48:11.351
why don't they hurry up and land?

429
00:48:26.033 --> 00:48:27.330
Tako-Chan...

430
00:48:27.668 --> 00:48:31.661
the four chicks that were born
two months ago have grown so much.

431
00:48:32.139 --> 00:48:36.166
The mother chicken leads them
for food every day...

432
00:48:36.677 --> 00:48:40.841
but they're giving me a hard time. picking
at the vegetable garden I have grown.

433
00:48:45.820 --> 00:48:49.153
The fleet of American ships
has left Saipan.

434
00:48:57.565 --> 00:48:59.226
So they are on their way.

435
00:49:00.868 --> 00:49:02.665
Ready the troops.

436
00:49:38.405 --> 00:49:39.565
Men...

437
00:49:40.908 --> 00:49:43.900
the time has come
to show your true colors.

438
00:49:44.879 --> 00:49:47.211
As a member of the honorable
lmperial Army...

439
00:49:47.948 --> 00:49:50.416
I trust that you will fight with honor.

440
00:49:53.654 --> 00:49:57.613
This island is of utmost importance
to Japan.

441
00:49:58.926 --> 00:50:00.291
Should the island fall...

442
00:50:02.596 --> 00:50:04.257
the enemy...

443
00:50:05.166 --> 00:50:09.262
will use it as their base
to attack our homeland.

444
00:50:10.671 --> 00:50:12.263
For the mainland...

445
00:50:13.741 --> 00:50:15.299
For our homeland...

446
00:50:15.843 --> 00:50:18.277
Until the very last man.

447
00:50:19.146 --> 00:50:22.309
Our duty is to stop the enemy right here.

448
00:50:23.717 --> 00:50:25.184
Not one of you...

449
00:50:25.819 --> 00:50:29.016
is allowed to die until you have killed
10 enemy soldiers.

450
00:50:33.060 --> 00:50:36.427
Do not expect to return home alive.

451
00:50:39.200 --> 00:50:43.034
I will always be in front of you.

452
00:50:52.179 --> 00:50:53.840
Long live the Emperor.

453
00:51:37.925 --> 00:51:41.258
Take care and be well.

454
00:51:42.763 --> 00:51:47.894
I will fight courageously until the end.
in the spirit of Yamato.

455
00:51:49.069 --> 00:51:53.438
My heart will always be with you.

456
00:51:54.475 --> 00:51:55.737
Takeichi.

457
00:52:12.126 --> 00:52:17.530
Every household is assigned a quota
of bag-making for the gunpowder.

458
00:52:18.299 --> 00:52:22.793
I cannot help but get tense when I think
that these will be used in battle.

459
00:52:23.637 --> 00:52:26.629
Taro and Yoko laugh at me for this.

460
00:52:27.541 --> 00:52:30.874
Takako. on evacuation in Nagano.
is also doing well.

461
00:52:31.679 --> 00:52:33.806
I pray for your safety.

462
00:52:34.815 --> 00:52:37.215
Sincerely. Yoshi.

463
00:52:51.131 --> 00:52:52.826
No one can shoot me now.

464
00:52:56.837 --> 00:53:01.069
That's a nice belt.
My wife sent me one. too.

465
00:53:05.813 --> 00:53:09.977
Doesn't look like Mr. Kempeitai
has a thousand-stitch belt. does he?

466
00:53:10.351 --> 00:53:12.842
Maybe he thinks it will clash
with his uniform.

467
00:53:13.020 --> 00:53:15.580
He probably doesn't believe
in superstitions. anyway.

468
00:53:20.527 --> 00:53:22.825
His mother made him one after all.

469
00:53:45.919 --> 00:53:49.082
- Maybe they're trying to sink the island.
- My head hurts.

470
00:53:49.356 --> 00:53:52.348
How many ships do you think
there are out there?

471
00:53:52.526 --> 00:53:56.223
At least 30. Maybe even 50.

472
00:53:56.563 --> 00:53:59.157
- They must be really close.
- I need to take a leak.

473
00:53:59.333 --> 00:54:02.063
Don't go near the sewers.
Dysentery is spreading through there.

474
00:54:02.236 --> 00:54:03.396
Where do I go then?

475
00:54:03.737 --> 00:54:05.728
There is a pot at the end of the cave.

476
00:54:26.093 --> 00:54:27.958
The shit pot is full.

477
00:54:28.262 --> 00:54:30.230
Someone needs to throw it out.

478
00:54:53.787 --> 00:54:56.187
If anything happens to that pot...

479
00:54:57.624 --> 00:55:02.527
you'll be carrying our shit away
with your hands.

480
00:56:09.563 --> 00:56:11.394
Is this some kind of a joke?

481
00:56:12.432 --> 00:56:14.900
Why are you always picking on me?

482
00:56:53.874 --> 00:56:58.334
Thank you. God. I take back
what I said before.

483
00:57:13.060 --> 00:57:14.891
Shall we commence fire?

484
00:57:15.262 --> 00:57:16.354
Not yet.

485
00:57:21.468 --> 00:57:24.062
The men wish to commence firing.

486
00:57:31.578 --> 00:57:32.909
Hold your fire!

487
00:57:36.249 --> 00:57:37.580
Hold your fire!

488
00:57:37.918 --> 00:57:39.249
Hold your fire!

489
00:57:47.294 --> 00:57:50.320
They will take the beach
in no time if we do not resist.

490
00:57:50.497 --> 00:57:52.488
Wait until the beach is full.

491
00:58:15.188 --> 00:58:18.089
Let's go. Commence firing!

492
00:58:24.031 --> 00:58:25.464
Commence firing!

493
00:58:26.600 --> 00:58:28.033
Commence firing!

494
00:59:30.163 --> 00:59:32.188
The guns of the Kitakubo unit
were destroyed.

495
00:59:32.365 --> 00:59:34.697
All the pillbox units on the beach
have been destroyed.

496
00:59:34.868 --> 00:59:36.768
However. all other forces are intact...

497
00:59:36.937 --> 00:59:39.201
and we estimate more than
1.000 enemy casualties.

498
00:59:39.706 --> 00:59:42.106
The pillbox destruction was unavoidable.

499
00:59:42.509 --> 00:59:44.602
Overall. that is good news.

500
00:59:44.878 --> 00:59:46.778
How are the men
holding up at Suribachi?

501
00:59:47.881 --> 00:59:49.246
Forces are intact.

502
00:59:53.019 --> 00:59:54.418
What is the enemy situation?

503
00:59:54.588 --> 00:59:57.580
Approximately 20.000 men and 80 tanks.

504
00:59:57.991 --> 01:00:02.223
There has to be more than that.
They still have men waiting in the boats.

505
01:00:02.429 --> 01:00:04.920
Currently the enemy front extends...

506
01:00:05.398 --> 01:00:08.094
between Suribachi
and the south landing...

507
01:00:08.635 --> 01:00:10.899
and chidori airfield south.

508
01:00:11.571 --> 01:00:15.769
Just as I thought... Suribachi
and the Motoyama airfield.

509
01:00:16.743 --> 01:00:19.041
They are making a two-pronged attack.

510
01:00:34.394 --> 01:00:37.557
That's not enough! I need more ammo.

511
01:01:02.789 --> 01:01:04.120
Take his place!

512
01:01:04.524 --> 01:01:06.651
- The machine gun is blasted.
- Use your rifle!

513
01:01:09.262 --> 01:01:10.786
Watch out! Lmbecile!

514
01:01:11.865 --> 01:01:13.093
I can't rely on you.

515
01:01:13.266 --> 01:01:16.463
Go send a report to colonel Adachi
that we need another machine gun.

516
01:01:16.870 --> 01:01:18.132
Hurry up!

517
01:01:44.564 --> 01:01:46.828
Colonel Adachi is asking
for reinforcements.

518
01:01:47.200 --> 01:01:51.500
We can't afford to send reinforcements.
Tell him to hold out.

519
01:02:02.883 --> 01:02:04.180
Shoot him!

520
01:02:12.192 --> 01:02:14.524
- What's the matter?
- We're out of bullets!

521
01:02:33.213 --> 01:02:35.204
We are losing Suribachi.

522
01:02:36.049 --> 01:02:40.383
All is lost. Request permission
to lead a suicide mission.

523
01:02:40.887 --> 01:02:43.879
No. You must try to hold them off.

524
01:02:44.624 --> 01:02:48.458
Do what you can to survive
and join forces in the north caves.

525
01:02:49.262 --> 01:02:50.354
But. sir...

526
01:02:51.064 --> 01:02:53.965
I have failed to hold Suribachi.

527
01:02:54.234 --> 01:02:57.135
Permit me to die with honor with my men.

528
01:02:57.470 --> 01:02:58.630
No. colonel.

529
01:02:59.306 --> 01:03:00.637
This is an order!

530
01:03:06.079 --> 01:03:07.239
Adachi.

531
01:03:09.416 --> 01:03:10.576
Adachi!

532
01:03:23.496 --> 01:03:27.523
Sir. captain Tanida
requests machine guns.

533
01:03:29.669 --> 01:03:30.966
It's over.

534
01:03:39.112 --> 01:03:40.306
Suicide...

535
01:03:41.681 --> 01:03:43.649
That's the only thing left.

536
01:03:44.584 --> 01:03:45.573
But...

537
01:03:46.920 --> 01:03:49.912
Here. take this to your commander.

538
01:04:34.868 --> 01:04:38.497
I heard General Kuribayashi
order colonel Adachi to escape.

539
01:04:38.671 --> 01:04:39.695
Quiet!

540
01:04:43.243 --> 01:04:46.508
Escape is the coward's way.

541
01:04:47.680 --> 01:04:48.908
Sit down!

542
01:05:01.061 --> 01:05:02.153
Men...

543
01:05:05.031 --> 01:05:06.089
we are...

544
01:05:08.935 --> 01:05:11.267
honorable soldiers of the Emperor.

545
01:05:15.008 --> 01:05:16.532
Don't ever forget that.

546
01:05:20.713 --> 01:05:22.613
The only way left for us...

547
01:05:24.551 --> 01:05:26.451
is to die with honor.

548
01:05:30.223 --> 01:05:31.713
This is our fate...

549
01:05:33.393 --> 01:05:35.725
to find our place at Yasukuni Shrine.

550
01:05:40.800 --> 01:05:42.461
I'll see you there.

551
01:06:02.255 --> 01:06:04.246
Soldiers. farewell!

552
01:07:59.539 --> 01:08:00.597
Stop!

553
01:08:08.214 --> 01:08:11.775
You should die like an honorable soldier.

554
01:08:12.685 --> 01:08:14.209
Look. Shimizu...

555
01:08:16.956 --> 01:08:19.754
we can still join the troops
in the northern caves.

556
01:08:20.727 --> 01:08:23.389
Our orders are to stay here until death.

557
01:08:23.563 --> 01:08:25.394
I heard General Kuribayashi himself.

558
01:08:26.532 --> 01:08:28.193
That's what he said...

559
01:08:30.036 --> 01:08:31.367
over the radio.

560
01:08:32.805 --> 01:08:34.067
It's true.

561
01:08:38.244 --> 01:08:40.405
We can die here...

562
01:08:42.048 --> 01:08:44.573
or we can continue fighting.

563
01:08:47.987 --> 01:08:50.888
Which would better serve the Emperor?

564
01:08:53.760 --> 01:08:55.250
Which one?

565
01:09:17.450 --> 01:09:18.815
Where does this go?

566
01:09:18.985 --> 01:09:21.283
It will take us closer to Motoyama.

567
01:09:27.360 --> 01:09:29.191
Do you have orders to move back?

568
01:09:30.630 --> 01:09:32.598
Where are the rest of your men?

569
01:09:33.099 --> 01:09:34.430
All dead.

570
01:09:35.968 --> 01:09:37.833
It's the same with us.

571
01:09:45.845 --> 01:09:48.109
There should be an outlet
somewhere near here.

572
01:09:48.314 --> 01:09:49.474
Be quiet!

573
01:10:37.196 --> 01:10:42.031
So you thought you could blow us up.
or burn us alive. did you?

574
01:10:57.717 --> 01:11:00.049
- Have we heard from Suribachi?
- No. sir.

575
01:11:00.219 --> 01:11:01.743
Send a messenger!

576
01:11:09.762 --> 01:11:13.721
Lieutenant oiso has ordered us
to rendezvous at the east cave.

577
01:11:21.908 --> 01:11:24.877
We will make a run for Motoyama.

578
01:11:25.578 --> 01:11:28.206
There is no cover for two kilometers.

579
01:11:28.948 --> 01:11:31.576
It will be every man for himself.

580
01:11:38.257 --> 01:11:40.088
See you on the other side.

581
01:11:40.760 --> 01:11:44.560
If not on this earth.
then in the next world.

582
01:11:59.512 --> 01:12:02.174
Don't run with the herd.
That's where the enemy will fire.

583
01:12:02.348 --> 01:12:03.576
Stay back.

584
01:12:04.383 --> 01:12:05.748
That's cowardice!

585
01:12:07.687 --> 01:12:11.214
There is no use for a dead soldier.

586
01:12:41.153 --> 01:12:43.314
Wait until the flare is gone.

587
01:13:09.448 --> 01:13:11.177
Crawl forward.

588
01:13:29.669 --> 01:13:31.193
What happened to the messenger?

589
01:13:31.437 --> 01:13:32.836
He never came back.

590
01:13:36.842 --> 01:13:38.434
I will go to Adachi myself.

591
01:13:38.711 --> 01:13:41.839
Motoyama's transmitter
still works. General.

592
01:13:43.082 --> 01:13:44.982
Why not try there. sir?

593
01:14:06.072 --> 01:14:08.063
Sir. these men retreated
from Mt. Suribachi.

594
01:14:15.181 --> 01:14:16.546
What are your names?

595
01:14:16.849 --> 01:14:19.374
Saigo. from the 312th.

596
01:14:20.019 --> 01:14:21.543
Shimizu. reporting for duty.

597
01:14:23.723 --> 01:14:25.714
You escaped from Suribachi?

598
01:14:32.198 --> 01:14:34.223
How dare you!

599
01:14:36.135 --> 01:14:39.070
It was your duty
to stay in your position until death.

600
01:14:41.374 --> 01:14:42.932
You should have died...

601
01:14:43.876 --> 01:14:46.242
with your fellow troop members.

602
01:14:47.446 --> 01:14:51.280
You are both a disgrace.

603
01:14:55.421 --> 01:14:56.911
Get on your knees.

604
01:14:59.558 --> 01:15:02.254
- But. sir...
- I said. get on your knees!

605
01:15:22.481 --> 01:15:24.915
I don't want you to kill
my soldiers needlessly.

606
01:15:26.619 --> 01:15:28.177
Put down your sword.

607
01:15:28.688 --> 01:15:30.019
Put it down!

608
01:15:36.429 --> 01:15:37.953
What's going on here?

609
01:15:40.299 --> 01:15:44.497
These men ran from Suribachi.

610
01:15:47.006 --> 01:15:51.841
Lt. Ito. I gave the order that all survivors
retreat to the north caves.

611
01:15:54.180 --> 01:15:55.841
I am very sorry. General.

612
01:15:58.117 --> 01:15:59.345
It's just...

613
01:16:00.653 --> 01:16:02.120
Suribachi...

614
01:16:04.490 --> 01:16:05.889
has fallen.

615
01:16:27.213 --> 01:16:28.874
Now that Suribachi has been taken...

616
01:16:29.048 --> 01:16:31.448
the enemy will maneuver all forces
onto the hillside.

617
01:16:31.617 --> 01:16:33.642
We must move
our command center north. sir.

618
01:16:40.025 --> 01:16:41.151
Ito...

619
01:16:43.295 --> 01:16:45.490
fight for your fallen brethren...

620
01:16:47.333 --> 01:16:49.028
until the end.

621
01:17:11.461 --> 01:17:12.928
Get up!

622
01:17:17.200 --> 01:17:19.259
Major General Hayashi
is leading an attack.

623
01:17:19.435 --> 01:17:21.027
We are to join him.

624
01:17:24.607 --> 01:17:26.973
Kuribayashi's orders are
to remain in the caves.

625
01:17:29.479 --> 01:17:33.779
Lieutenant lto says Kuribayashi
is a weak American sympathizer.

626
01:17:43.693 --> 01:17:46.526
We will take back Mt. Suribachi.

627
01:18:08.651 --> 01:18:10.676
Where is Major General Hayashi?

628
01:18:13.256 --> 01:18:14.621
We don't know. sir.

629
01:18:15.258 --> 01:18:16.691
Who is in charge here?

630
01:18:16.926 --> 01:18:18.826
I'm not sure.

631
01:18:21.998 --> 01:18:24.330
Stay here until
I determine the plan of action.

632
01:18:50.092 --> 01:18:51.582
We're dead.

633
01:18:57.567 --> 01:18:59.694
Pull back!

634
01:19:00.236 --> 01:19:02.067
We'll get reinforcements.

635
01:19:34.403 --> 01:19:39.238
Why didn't your regiment join the attack?

636
01:19:43.279 --> 01:19:44.974
Don't sit here like rats!

637
01:19:45.848 --> 01:19:49.443
Come out of your caves and fight!

638
01:19:51.253 --> 01:19:52.811
Where is your commander?

639
01:19:52.989 --> 01:19:54.854
We haven't received the order to attack.

640
01:19:58.527 --> 01:20:01.291
Didn't you receive the order
from General Hayashi?

641
01:20:02.698 --> 01:20:05.792
Kuribayashi countermanded
Hayashi's order.

642
01:20:06.335 --> 01:20:08.269
There is to be no attack.

643
01:20:11.941 --> 01:20:14.102
We will take back Suribachi...

644
01:20:15.044 --> 01:20:16.671
with or without Kuribayashi.

645
01:20:17.380 --> 01:20:20.611
There are already troops on the attack.
Get your men in order.

646
01:20:20.783 --> 01:20:23.411
Lieutenant. may I remind you
of your rank!

647
01:20:23.619 --> 01:20:25.985
Your disrespect for senior officers...

648
01:20:26.822 --> 01:20:29.620
puts your men at needless risk.

649
01:20:31.661 --> 01:20:33.652
I suggest you go back to your cave...

650
01:20:33.829 --> 01:20:37.697
or hand over your men.

651
01:20:47.910 --> 01:20:49.138
Enough.

652
01:20:49.545 --> 01:20:51.274
We'll do it ourselves.

653
01:21:02.391 --> 01:21:03.756
That's against regulations.

654
01:21:04.093 --> 01:21:07.688
That's the officer who tried to kill us.
He doesn't care.

655
01:21:39.862 --> 01:21:41.227
I won't go back.

656
01:21:43.265 --> 01:21:45.460
I've had enough of cave fighting.

657
01:21:47.703 --> 01:21:50.570
You men are now under
Lieutenant colonel Nishi's command.

658
01:22:02.651 --> 01:22:04.516
I will throw myself under an enemy tank.

659
01:22:08.124 --> 01:22:10.649
I will take out one of their machines.

660
01:22:39.288 --> 01:22:40.516
Hurry.

661
01:22:42.925 --> 01:22:44.324
What is the status?

662
01:22:46.128 --> 01:22:47.857
A thousand men were lost...

663
01:22:48.030 --> 01:22:49.930
in a night attack along chidori airfield.

664
01:22:50.099 --> 01:22:52.863
Why? I have given them strict orders
not to kill themselves.

665
01:22:53.035 --> 01:22:56.801
It seems that the order to retreat
was not conveyed to all sectors.

666
01:22:57.673 --> 01:22:58.935
Hayashi.

667
01:22:59.441 --> 01:23:00.772
Damn you!

668
01:23:01.844 --> 01:23:03.334
And the American advancement?

669
01:23:03.946 --> 01:23:07.712
A battalion is headed north and we
are fighting back along the west ridge.

670
01:23:07.883 --> 01:23:12.149
Good. Once they cross the west ridge.
they will be surrounded on three sides.

671
01:23:13.556 --> 01:23:14.853
This just arrived.

672
01:23:15.024 --> 01:23:16.150
Read it.

673
01:23:21.130 --> 01:23:22.654
From headquarters...

674
01:23:24.834 --> 01:23:29.498
"we regret that we are unable to send
reinforcements to IWO at this time.

675
01:23:30.906 --> 01:23:34.398
We earnestly hope you will
fight honorably...

676
01:23:35.177 --> 01:23:37.372
and die for your country."

677
01:25:19.448 --> 01:25:20.540
Bring him in.

678
01:25:36.365 --> 01:25:37.354
Bring him in.

679
01:25:47.810 --> 01:25:49.971
Shall I finish him off?

680
01:25:50.713 --> 01:25:52.704
No. Treat him.

681
01:25:54.149 --> 01:25:55.377
But. sir...

682
01:25:55.551 --> 01:25:58.179
okubo. you would expect the same.
wouldn't you?

683
01:25:58.354 --> 01:25:59.651
Endo. treat him.

684
01:26:00.055 --> 01:26:02.853
We are low on morphine as it is.

685
01:26:04.326 --> 01:26:07.159
Sir. the Americans would not treat
a wounded Japanese soldier.

686
01:26:07.329 --> 01:26:10.298
Son. have you ever met one?

687
01:26:11.834 --> 01:26:12.960
Treat him.

688
01:26:50.439 --> 01:26:52.532
Where are you. American tanks?

689
01:26:53.609 --> 01:26:55.236
Come and get me!

690
01:27:10.893 --> 01:27:12.520
How is the prisoner doing?

691
01:27:13.028 --> 01:27:14.359
He is awake. sir.

692
01:27:18.300 --> 01:27:21.463
I will question the prisoner
for information.

693
01:29:08.010 --> 01:29:09.238
Damn.

694
01:29:11.613 --> 01:29:13.103
I've had enough of this.

695
01:29:13.849 --> 01:29:15.407
I'm going to surrender.

696
01:29:20.122 --> 01:29:22.056
Go ahead and arrest me.

697
01:29:23.292 --> 01:29:27.058
I don't care anymore. That's what
you were put here for. isn't it?

698
01:29:28.463 --> 01:29:30.931
To report treasonous thoughts.

699
01:29:35.437 --> 01:29:37.234
I was put here because...

700
01:29:38.707 --> 01:29:40.800
I was discharged from the Kempeitai.

701
01:29:44.079 --> 01:29:45.239
Discharged?

702
01:29:49.885 --> 01:29:53.150
I had only been in service
for five days.

703
01:29:56.425 --> 01:29:57.483
Shimizu...

704
01:29:57.659 --> 01:30:00.423
you must always be firm.

705
01:30:01.563 --> 01:30:05.761
Any mercy and people
will take advantage of you.

706
01:30:11.273 --> 01:30:12.433
That's unpatriotic.

707
01:30:12.741 --> 01:30:14.265
Go sort it out. Shimizu.

708
01:30:26.955 --> 01:30:29.788
You do not have the lmperial flag
properly displayed.

709
01:30:29.958 --> 01:30:31.186
I'm sorry.

710
01:30:31.360 --> 01:30:34.887
My husband has gone to war
and I couldn't put it up myself.

711
01:30:35.063 --> 01:30:37.759
It is unpatriotic
not to have the flag displayed.

712
01:30:37.933 --> 01:30:40.197
If you help me. I'll put it up now.

713
01:31:00.722 --> 01:31:02.656
Get that dog to shut up.

714
01:31:04.226 --> 01:31:05.420
What was that. sir?

715
01:31:06.561 --> 01:31:10.827
That dog is a nuisance.
It is disruptive of Army communications.

716
01:31:11.400 --> 01:31:13.459
I am very sorry. sir.

717
01:31:19.841 --> 01:31:21.934
Shimizu. Dispose of the dog.

718
01:31:23.245 --> 01:31:26.806
We can't have a dog interfering
with important military commands.

719
01:31:32.587 --> 01:31:34.214
Take the dog in the back.

720
01:31:34.556 --> 01:31:35.921
It's only a dog.

721
01:31:36.158 --> 01:31:38.718
It won't happen again.

722
01:31:39.194 --> 01:31:40.593
Take it out back.

723
01:31:41.096 --> 01:31:42.757
Keep the children inside.

724
01:31:43.932 --> 01:31:45.194
Hurry up.

725
01:32:33.515 --> 01:32:35.813
Take the dog into the house
and keep him quiet...

726
01:32:36.551 --> 01:32:37.540
and never let him out.

727
01:32:49.731 --> 01:32:51.255
It's taken care of. sir.

728
01:33:29.638 --> 01:33:31.538
Are you trying to make a fool out of me?

729
01:33:33.408 --> 01:33:38.710
If you can't even shoot a dog.
you'll never be able to handle the Reds.

730
01:33:40.482 --> 01:33:41.881
You are unpatriotic!

731
01:33:48.123 --> 01:33:50.489
I was discharged for insubordination...

732
01:33:51.693 --> 01:33:53.388
and sent here.

733
01:34:02.204 --> 01:34:03.967
Don't look so glum. Shimizu.

734
01:34:05.507 --> 01:34:08.135
At least now only the enemy hates you.

735
01:34:13.248 --> 01:34:15.011
I don't blame the dog.

736
01:34:40.775 --> 01:34:41.935
Taro...

737
01:34:42.377 --> 01:34:45.278
tonight I attended my farewell party.

738
01:34:45.914 --> 01:34:48.439
The wives also attended.
so there was a lot of fuss.

739
01:34:48.617 --> 01:34:51.552
Greeting all the ladies...

740
01:34:51.786 --> 01:34:54.914
kept me from enjoying the food.

741
01:37:40.021 --> 01:37:42.046
Is there any information
of the enemy's plan?

742
01:37:42.857 --> 01:37:45.052
No. it's just a letter.

743
01:37:46.928 --> 01:37:48.725
It's from his mother.

744
01:37:51.199 --> 01:37:52.257
"Sam...

745
01:37:53.301 --> 01:37:55.667
I have mailed you
a couple of books to read.

746
01:37:56.271 --> 01:37:57.795
I hope that you like them.

747
01:37:59.207 --> 01:38:00.196
Yesterday...

748
01:38:00.942 --> 01:38:05.709
the dogs dug a hole under the fence.

749
01:38:07.082 --> 01:38:11.314
They ran all over the neighborhood.

750
01:38:12.420 --> 01:38:14.615
By the time we found them...

751
01:38:15.824 --> 01:38:20.818
the Harrisons' roosters were terrorized.

752
01:38:21.629 --> 01:38:24.462
Don't worry about us.

753
01:38:25.734 --> 01:38:29.795
Just take care of yourself
and come back safely.

754
01:38:30.171 --> 01:38:33.902
Remember what I said to you...

755
01:38:37.512 --> 01:38:39.139
always do what is right...

756
01:38:40.248 --> 01:38:42.443
because it is right.

757
01:38:43.618 --> 01:38:47.281
I pray for a speedy end to the war...

758
01:38:47.455 --> 01:38:48.854
and your safe return.

759
01:38:50.458 --> 01:38:51.789
Love. Mom."

760
01:39:26.461 --> 01:39:29.055
I'm sorry. sir. There is no more medicine.

761
01:39:29.230 --> 01:39:32.393
It's all right. I'm useless now.
Go help the others!

762
01:41:03.758 --> 01:41:05.783
Okubo. come here.

763
01:41:12.500 --> 01:41:14.263
How are we on ammunition?

764
01:41:16.337 --> 01:41:18.771
Not good. sir.

765
01:41:20.308 --> 01:41:22.276
Our mortars have been taken out...

766
01:41:23.077 --> 01:41:24.942
and we're out of machine gun ammo.

767
01:41:26.748 --> 01:41:30.081
We have only our rifles.

768
01:41:32.153 --> 01:41:33.142
Okubo...

769
01:41:33.321 --> 01:41:37.121
you are now in charge of the men.

770
01:41:41.863 --> 01:41:43.455
We can no longer hold this area.

771
01:41:44.198 --> 01:41:47.690
You must guide
the rest of the men north.

772
01:41:50.371 --> 01:41:53.772
Take whatever food and ammo
we have left.

773
01:41:54.943 --> 01:41:57.309
What about you. sir?

774
01:42:00.715 --> 01:42:04.151
I'm tired of sharing this cave
with all of you.

775
01:42:04.986 --> 01:42:07.511
I'm a one-man show from here on out.

776
01:42:07.855 --> 01:42:09.618
What are you talking about. sir?

777
01:42:10.992 --> 01:42:14.291
Your first order of business...

778
01:42:15.330 --> 01:42:17.059
is to find some water.

779
01:42:44.058 --> 01:42:45.218
Men...

780
01:42:46.694 --> 01:42:48.321
do your best.

781
01:42:49.831 --> 01:42:54.234
Do what is right...

782
01:42:56.070 --> 01:42:58.334
because it is right.

783
01:43:00.508 --> 01:43:01.736
Understood?

784
01:43:09.550 --> 01:43:14.510
I will make sure that they send you
medicine and food.

785
01:43:16.758 --> 01:43:18.089
It has been a great honor...

786
01:43:19.527 --> 01:43:20.755
to serve...

787
01:43:22.063 --> 01:43:23.530
under you.

788
01:44:02.670 --> 01:44:04.228
Hand me my rifle.

789
01:44:28.029 --> 01:44:29.929
I'm sorry. okubo.

790
01:45:50.044 --> 01:45:53.241
Why am I not getting any reports?
Have we heard from Admiral Ichimaru?

791
01:45:53.414 --> 01:45:56.178
- No. sir.
- What about Nishi or Hayashi?

792
01:45:58.619 --> 01:46:01.679
- Send out messengers!
- We have. Many times.

793
01:46:01.923 --> 01:46:03.652
None of them have come back.

794
01:46:04.158 --> 01:46:05.921
You can't plan strategy like this!

795
01:46:17.104 --> 01:46:20.596
I have been thinking about
what Lt. Colonel Nishi said.

796
01:46:21.375 --> 01:46:22.774
He's right.

797
01:46:28.049 --> 01:46:30.950
I don't know anything about the enemy.

798
01:46:31.719 --> 01:46:35.382
I believed that the Americans
were cowards...

799
01:46:41.529 --> 01:46:43.292
but they weren't.

800
01:46:48.536 --> 01:46:50.697
I was taught...

801
01:46:52.340 --> 01:46:54.069
that they were savages...

802
01:46:55.876 --> 01:46:57.844
but that American soldier...

803
01:47:05.353 --> 01:47:07.480
his mother's words...

804
01:47:11.425 --> 01:47:13.552
were the same as my mother's.

805
01:47:14.762 --> 01:47:18.755
I want to fulfill my duty
for the general...

806
01:47:19.667 --> 01:47:21.828
and our country...

807
01:47:23.571 --> 01:47:25.698
but I don't want to die for nothing.

808
01:47:31.712 --> 01:47:33.077
What do you think?

809
01:47:45.293 --> 01:47:46.385
You...

810
01:47:47.695 --> 01:47:50.459
haven't lived enough to realize...

811
01:47:55.303 --> 01:47:57.771
what you are sacrificing.

812
01:48:06.113 --> 01:48:08.308
Will you surrender with me?

813
01:48:29.737 --> 01:48:31.068
Careful.

814
01:48:34.675 --> 01:48:38.475
They'll notice if we leave together.
You go first.

815
01:48:39.447 --> 01:48:41.210
I'll make up an excuse.

816
01:48:41.382 --> 01:48:44.010
After a while. I'll tell them
I'm going to check on you.

817
01:48:44.185 --> 01:48:46.176
We'll be gone before they even notice.

818
01:48:49.590 --> 01:48:51.615
Pretend that you have dysentery.

819
01:48:52.460 --> 01:48:54.690
Give me your dysentery look.

820
01:49:04.638 --> 01:49:06.299
I guess that'll have to do.

821
01:49:15.282 --> 01:49:16.840
Where are you going?

822
01:49:17.184 --> 01:49:18.811
I've got dysentery.

823
01:49:19.286 --> 01:49:21.220
You're going to surrender. aren't you?

824
01:49:21.389 --> 01:49:23.482
If you are. take me with you.

825
01:49:24.125 --> 01:49:26.719
- I've had enough of this war.
- Be quiet!

826
01:49:35.202 --> 01:49:37.693
Where are you going?

827
01:49:37.938 --> 01:49:40.406
He said he wasn't feeling well.
It could be dysentery.

828
01:49:40.574 --> 01:49:41.836
You two! Stop!

829
01:49:47.615 --> 01:49:48.912
Sir. maybe they got spooked.

830
01:50:06.200 --> 01:50:08.668
Miura. you're on guard.

831
01:50:09.336 --> 01:50:11.327
Make sure we have no more deserters.

832
01:51:37.625 --> 01:51:39.252
What unit were you with?

833
01:51:42.096 --> 01:51:45.998
Higashiyama 314th.

834
01:51:55.709 --> 01:51:57.142
Did you hear...

835
01:51:58.846 --> 01:52:02.441
I heard that they would give you a meal.

836
01:52:04.451 --> 01:52:05.679
A meal...

837
01:52:09.857 --> 01:52:11.552
That sounds good.

838
01:52:16.564 --> 01:52:18.225
I'm from Yokohama. too.

839
01:52:21.669 --> 01:52:24.968
After this is over. you can come visit me.

840
01:53:41.281 --> 01:53:42.475
Lieutenant!

841
01:54:24.124 --> 01:54:25.921
Let this be a lesson to anyone else...

842
01:54:28.162 --> 01:54:29.789
who wants to surrender.

843
01:55:42.703 --> 01:55:46.571
We need to get through the crossfire
to reach the north...

844
01:55:47.441 --> 01:55:49.136
and join our forces at the front.

845
01:55:55.182 --> 01:55:56.274
Listen.

846
01:55:57.351 --> 01:55:59.842
We'll head for that cave
and make our way from there.

847
01:56:03.390 --> 01:56:04.948
Don't waste a bullet!

848
01:56:06.126 --> 01:56:07.559
Not a single one.

849
01:56:08.128 --> 01:56:09.686
Don't shoot recklessly.

850
01:57:10.357 --> 01:57:14.418
These are Nishi's troops
and the survivors from Suribachi.

851
01:57:18.532 --> 01:57:20.500
Are there no officers?

852
01:57:24.338 --> 01:57:26.602
You all did a good job making it here.

853
01:57:27.674 --> 01:57:29.335
Fujita. water for them.

854
01:57:33.981 --> 01:57:36.882
I'm sorry. sir. There is no more water.

855
01:57:40.721 --> 01:57:41.813
I'm sorry.

856
01:57:43.156 --> 01:57:44.487
At least you can rest.

857
01:57:59.673 --> 01:58:01.300
You look familiar.

858
01:58:06.546 --> 01:58:08.138
You almost lost your head.

859
01:58:11.184 --> 01:58:15.245
That was the second time you saved me.

860
01:58:18.058 --> 01:58:19.491
The first time...

861
01:58:20.193 --> 01:58:23.822
was the day you landed on the island.

862
01:58:27.601 --> 01:58:29.535
Of course. I remember.

863
01:58:31.204 --> 01:58:32.831
Well. everything happens in threes.

864
01:58:49.523 --> 01:58:50.854
Hanako...

865
01:58:51.892 --> 01:58:54.292
This letter will probably
never get to you...

866
01:58:55.028 --> 01:58:56.017
but...

867
01:58:56.730 --> 01:58:58.960
it comforts me to write.

868
01:59:00.434 --> 01:59:02.959
For five days. we've been
without water and food.

869
01:59:04.271 --> 01:59:06.034
To survive...

870
01:59:07.808 --> 01:59:09.867
we do unspeakable things.

871
01:59:12.879 --> 01:59:14.710
There is no escape now.

872
01:59:15.482 --> 01:59:16.642
But...

873
01:59:17.884 --> 01:59:20.717
my only concern is for you and the baby.

874
01:59:27.260 --> 01:59:28.818
Dig up some worms.

875
01:59:47.914 --> 01:59:50.610
The battle is approaching its end...

876
01:59:51.184 --> 01:59:53.914
and there is no more ammunition.
no more water.

877
01:59:54.087 --> 01:59:57.579
All the survivors will engage
in a general attack.

878
01:59:58.925 --> 02:00:02.361
I pray for the victory
and safety of the Empire.

879
02:00:02.963 --> 02:00:05.090
I bid you farewell.

880
02:00:06.767 --> 02:00:10.828
For the country.
I could not fulfill all of my duties.

881
02:00:11.004 --> 02:00:14.940
Now that we have no ammunition.
it is with regret that we must perish.

882
02:00:21.448 --> 02:00:24.611
You made it all the way from Suribachi?

883
02:00:27.521 --> 02:00:29.716
That must have been quite a journey.

884
02:00:35.462 --> 02:00:37.054
You are quite a soldier.

885
02:00:39.399 --> 02:00:40.798
No. sir.

886
02:00:41.868 --> 02:00:43.199
I'm just a simple baker.

887
02:00:44.004 --> 02:00:45.801
You were a baker?

888
02:00:47.307 --> 02:00:48.365
Any family?

889
02:00:49.409 --> 02:00:50.706
A wife...

890
02:00:51.311 --> 02:00:55.873
and a baby girl born
last summer in ohmiya.

891
02:00:59.352 --> 02:01:00.979
I haven't met her yet.

892
02:01:07.260 --> 02:01:08.659
It's strange.

893
02:01:11.231 --> 02:01:14.758
I promised myself to fight
until death for my family...

894
02:01:16.670 --> 02:01:21.004
but the thought of my family
makes it difficult to keep that promise.

895
02:01:44.397 --> 02:01:46.365
A radio transmission from the homeland.

896
02:02:00.046 --> 02:02:01.513
For General Kuribayashi...

897
02:02:01.681 --> 02:02:06.050
and his troops. who are fighting bravely
for our country...

898
02:02:06.219 --> 02:02:10.815
a song will be sung by the children of
Nagano. which is Kuribayashi's hometown.

899
02:02:11.158 --> 02:02:15.288
On the waves of the Pacific

900
02:02:15.462 --> 02:02:18.727
down south from the Imperial City

901
02:02:19.266 --> 02:02:23.930
a small lonely island floats

902
02:02:27.340 --> 02:02:30.969
The fate of our Imperial country

903
02:02:31.144 --> 02:02:35.808
lies in the hands of this island

904
02:02:38.618 --> 02:02:41.246
Iwo Jima

905
02:02:44.791 --> 02:02:48.283
As long as we stand

906
02:02:48.762 --> 02:02:52.858
we shall feel safe. as the Imperial land

907
02:02:53.033 --> 02:02:57.697
shall forever be at peace

908
02:03:00.974 --> 02:03:05.638
We shall fight with pride
and honor at any price

909
02:03:08.048 --> 02:03:11.609
Our proud island

910
02:03:12.219 --> 02:03:14.881
Iwo Jima

911
02:03:37.210 --> 02:03:38.541
Do me a favor.

912
02:03:40.213 --> 02:03:43.979
Stay here and burn all these documents.
and my military chest.

913
02:03:45.151 --> 02:03:47.312
Everything happens in threes.

914
02:04:16.783 --> 02:04:18.808
We will make a general attack.

915
02:04:19.886 --> 02:04:22.218
Although Japan has lost...

916
02:04:22.956 --> 02:04:24.821
one day...

917
02:04:25.692 --> 02:04:27.819
our people will praise your dedication.

918
02:04:28.962 --> 02:04:32.989
A day will come when they
will weep and pray for your souls.

919
02:04:35.702 --> 02:04:38.000
Be proud to die for your country.

920
02:04:45.145 --> 02:04:47.636
I will always be in front of you.

921
02:07:30.276 --> 02:07:31.504
No more.

922
02:07:33.713 --> 02:07:34.702
No more.

923
02:07:42.789 --> 02:07:44.484
Thank you. Fujita.

924
02:08:16.623 --> 02:08:17.783
This is an order.

925
02:09:26.259 --> 02:09:27.453
You again.

926
02:09:30.930 --> 02:09:34.696
I have one more favor to ask of you.

927
02:09:36.769 --> 02:09:37.963
Bury me...

928
02:09:39.105 --> 02:09:41.096
so that no one will find me.

929
02:09:55.688 --> 02:09:56.677
Taro...

930
02:09:57.123 --> 02:09:58.556
I will be home soon.

931
02:09:59.826 --> 02:10:01.817
I'm glad to be going back to Japan...

932
02:10:02.795 --> 02:10:06.196
but I'm a bit sad
to leave my friends behind.

933
02:10:09.669 --> 02:10:11.227
I drove home...

934
02:10:12.372 --> 02:10:13.361
but...

935
02:10:13.806 --> 02:10:16.400
it's lonely driving all by myself.

936
02:10:28.855 --> 02:10:30.846
Is this still Japanese soil?

937
02:10:40.366 --> 02:10:42.095
This is still Japan.

938
02:14:03.035 --> 02:14:04.400
Be careful.

941
02:14:05.305 --> 02:15:05.748
